Paul A. PORTER, Administrator of the Office of Price Administration, Appellant, v. Texas J. COLE, Doing Business as Liquor Warehouse, Appellee. No. 11747. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 13, 1946. David London, Director, Litigation Division, O. P. A., and Albert M. Dreyer, Chief Appellate Branch, O. P. A., both of Washington, D. C., Leonard M. Cox, Regional Litigation Atty., O. P. A., and Milton G. Mell and Walter B. Branan, Attys., O. P. A., all of Dallas, Texas, for appellant. Emil Corenbleth, of Dallas, Texas, for appellee.

Before PIUTCHESON, HOLMES, and McCORD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment, 66 F.Supp. 11, affirmed.
